    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi Dei aeterni. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName> divina
                        favente clementia <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Quia regalis celsitudo
                        opressis et necessitatem patientibus sublevationis atque defensionis
                        auxilium semper prebere debet, noverit omnium fidelium sancte Dei Eclesie
                        nostrorumque presentium scilicet hac futurorum industria, hoc homines, id
                        sunt: <persName key="#Other_palatine_officer #Judge"><name ref="Leo"
                                >Leo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex</rs> domni regis et <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer"
                            >vicedomino</rs> sancte <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/116"><placeName
                                ref="#places/245">Novariensis</placeName> eclesie</orgName>,
                            <persName key="#Scabini"><name ref="Guarnibertus"
                            >Vuarnempertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Scabini">scavinus</rs>, <persName key="#Local_elites"><name
                                ref="Petronax  de Galiate">Petronaus</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Teudebertus de Galiate"
                            >Teupertus</name></persName> germanis, <persName key="#Local_elites"
                                ><name ref="Domnulus">Domnolo</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Benedictus de Galiate"
                            >Benedictus</name></persName>, item <persName key="#Local_elites"><name
                                ref="Benedictus quondam Uuetti  de Galiate"
                            >Benedictus</name></persName> filius quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Uuetti">Uvedei</name></persName>, et tercio <persName
                            key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Benedictus de Galiate"
                            >Benedictus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Local_elites"><name
                                ref="Angelbertus de Galiate">Angelbertus</name></persName>, item
                            <persName key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Angelbertus de Galiate"
                                >Angelbertus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Local_elites"><name
                                ref="Ursus de Galiate">Ursus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Walpertus de Galiate"
                            >Vualpertus</name></persName> germanis, <persName key="#Local_elites"
                                ><name ref="Aredeo de Galiate">Aredeo</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Peredeo de Galiate"
                            >Peredeo</name></persName>, <persName key="#Local_elites"><name
                                ref="Dominicus de Galiate">Dominicus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Stefanus de Galiate"
                            >Stephanus</name></persName> germanis, item <persName
                            key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Stefanus de Galiate"
                            >Stephanus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Local_elites"><name
                                ref="Senepertus de Galiate">Simpertus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Notary"><name ref="Gausus de Galiate">Gausus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>, <persName key="#Local_elites"><name
                                ref="Widelbertus de Galiate">Vuidelbertus</name></persName>, item
                            <persName key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Teudebertus de Galiate"
                                >Teupertus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Local_elites"><name
                                ref="Walfredus de Galiate">Vualfredus</name></persName> germanis,
                            <persName key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Theodradus de Galiate"
                                >Teuderadus</name></persName>, habitatores in vico <placeName
                            ref="#places/601">Galiate</placeName>, <persName key="#Local_elites"
                                ><name ref="Wido de Berconate">Vuido</name></persName> de ipso loco,
                            <persName key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Rinfrido de Berconate"
                                >Rimfredus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Local_elites"><name
                                ref="Amalfredus de Berconate">Amelfredus</name></persName> et
                            <persName key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Martinus de Berconate"
                                >Martinus</name></persName> germanis, <persName key="#Local_elites"
                                ><name ref="Albertus de Berconate">Alpertus</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Local_elites"><name ref="Arisusus de Berconate"
                                >Arisusus</name></persName> de vico <placeName ref="#places/602"
                            >Berconate</placeName>, ad nos venerunt postulantes atque [pet]entes,
                        pro persecucione Paganorum atque malorum Christianorum virorum licentiam
                        daremus in suorum proprietatem <rs key="#Castle #Right_to_fortify">castellum
                            hedificandi</rs>. Quorum peticionibus pro Dei amore nostreque anime
                        mercede assensum prebentes, ut <rs key="#Castle">castrum</rs>,<rs
                            key="#Defensive_elements"> propugnacula, bertiscas</rs> ad expugnandum,
                        prout volunt, hedificent concessimus, per huius paginam inscriptionis
                        iubentes atque precipientes, <rs key="#Immunity">ut nullus <rs key="#Count"
                                >comes</rs>, <rs key="#Viscount">vicecomes</rs> atque <rs
                                key="#Sculdahis">sculdassio</rs> nullusque publicus [minister] vel
                            quelibet magna parvaque persona predictos homines suorumque heredes
                            super hoc distringere, molestare, aut aliquid exquerire quod iniustum
                            aut contra legem videtur aliquo modo presumat, sed liceat eis in ipso
                            castro residentibus pro mercede anime nostre quiete vivere absque
                            publica inquietudine</rs>; ita ut nullus audeat in ipso castro eos
                        pignorare, aut violenter intrare, aut placitum inibi tenere, aut in eorum
                        mansionibus sedere absque eorum voluntate pertemptet, sed liceat eis sub
                        nostro <rs key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">mundburdo</rs> pro mercede
                        anime nostre quiete vivere et manere. Si quis autem contra hoc nostrum
                        mundburdum predictos homines inquietare aut molestare vel pignorare aut
                        angariare presumpserit, vel quicquam quod iniustum aut contra legem videtur
                        eis fecerit, <rs key="#Penalty">C libras auri</rs> agnoscat se esse
                        compositurum, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem camere nostre</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera">medietatem predictis hominibus</rs> suorumque heredibus
                        vel cui super hoc aliqua fuerit ingesta molestia. Quod ut verius credatur
                        [et] diligentius observetur, manu propria roborantes de anulo nostro subter
                        insigniri iussimus. Signum domni Beengarii serenissimi regis. <persName
                            key="#Notary" ref="#people/1501">Iohannes</persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> iussu regio recognovi et subscripsi. Data
                        XIIII kal. Aug., anno incarnationis dominice DCCCCXI, domni vero Berengarii
                        serenissimi regis XXIIII, indictione XIIII. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/245">Novaria</placeName>. In Christi nomine feliciter.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
